class="post-210513 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-csr-3p tag-consumer-engagement tag-fashion-industry tag-history tag-levis-strauss tag-nike tag-sustainable-fashion tag-sustainable-fashion-2014" id="post-210513"><h2><a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/brief-history-sustainable-fashion/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to A Brief History of Sustainable Fashion"><span
itemprop="name">A Brief History of Sustainable Fashion</span></a></h2><div
class="meta"><div
class="authorImg"> <img
alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/6e435c79ef5bba75b32dad143274333e?s=18&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D18&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-18 photo' height='18' width='18' /></div><div
class="authorInfo"><h5><a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/author/nayelli-gonzalez/"><span
itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person"> <span
itemprop="name">Nayelli Gonzalez</span></a> |  Thursday February 19th, 2015 | <a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/brief-history-sustainable-fashion/#comments" title="Comments on A Brief History of Sustainable Fashion"><span
class="dsq-postid" data-dsqidentifier="210513 http://www.triplepundit.com/?p=210513">1 Comment</span></a></h5></div></div><div
class="entry"><div
class="bottomcontainerBox" style="border:1px solid #808080;background-color:#F0F4F9;"><div
style="float:left; width:85px;padding-right:10px; margin:4px 4px 4px 4px;height:30px;"> <iframe
src="http://www.facebook.com/plugins/like.php?href=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.triplepundit.com%2F2015%2F02%2Fbrief-history-sustainable-fashion%2F&amp;layout=button_count&amp;show_faces=false&amp;width=85&amp;action=like&amp;font=verdana&amp;colorscheme=light&amp;height=21" scrolling="no" frameborder="0" style="border:none; overflow:hidden; width=85px; height:21px;" allowTransparency="true"></iframe></div><div
style="float:left; width:80px;padding-right:10px; margin:4px 4px 4px 4px;height:30px;"> <g:plusone size="medium" href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/brief-history-sustainable-fashion/"></g:plusone></div><div
style="float:left; width:95px;padding-right:10px; margin:4px 4px 4px 4px;height:30px;"> <a
href="http://twitter.com/share" class="twitter-share-button" data-url="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/brief-history-sustainable-fashion/"  data-text="A Brief History of Sustainable Fashion" data-count="horizontal" data-via="triplepundit">Tweet</a></div><div
style="float:left; width:105px;padding-right:10px; margin:4px 4px 4px 4px;height:30px;"><script type="in/share" data-url="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/brief-history-sustainable-fashion/" data-counter="right"></script></div></div><div
style="clear:both"></div><div
style="padding-bottom:4px;"></div><div
style="text-align: right; font-size: .9em;"><a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/topic/sustainable-fashion-2014/"><img
class="alignnone" src="http://cdn6.triplepundit.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/topper1.jpg" alt="banner-mobile-innovation" width="650" height="75" />Read more in this series</a></div><div
id="attachment_210525" style="width: 285px" class="wp-caption alignright"><img
class="wp-image-210525 size-medium" src="http://cdn6.triplepundit.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/ad-275x300.jpg" alt="ad" width="275" height="300" /><p
class="wp-caption-text">An ad printed in the pages of Vogue magazine in 1967 inviting consumers to think of fashion as an investment.</p></div><p>Type the words ‘future’ and ‘fashion’ into any search engine, and you’ll get a stream of results on 3-D printing, wearable technology and e-commerce websites – sustainability is but a mere mention. Yet, the S-word has undeniably made its way into the modern apparel-making process and increasingly influences what lands on runways and store racks.</p><p><a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/topic/sustainable-fashion-2014/" target="_blank">The fashion industry</a>’s growing focus on sustainable practices has even prompted business publications such as Forbes to hail “<a
href="http://www.forbes.com/sites/aliciaadamczyk/2014/11/17/green-is-the-new-black-fashion-industry-aims-to-increase-sustainable-practices/" target="_blank">Green is the New Black</a>.”</p><p>Through innovative business practices, the fashion industry has come a long way in improving environmental and social conditions along complex global supply chains. Still, it has a way to go. A brief look into the industry’s storied past illuminates how <a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2013/08/5-lessons-kering-unknown-sustainability-leader/" target="_blank">corporate style setters</a> have responded to shifting consumer demands, market trends and natural resource constraints over the years – signaling what the future of sustainable fashion might hold.</p> <a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/brief-history-sustainable-fashion/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to A Brief History of Sustainable Fashion"> Click to continue reading &raquo;</a><p
class="more"><img
src="http://www.triplepundit.com/wp-content/themes/triplepunditv2/images/page_white_text.png"  alt="Permalink" /> <a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/brief-history-sustainable-fashion/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to A Brief History of Sustainable Fashion"> CONTINUES &raquo;</a> <img
alt="discuss" src="http://www.triplepundit.com/wp-content/themes/triplepunditv2/images/usergroup2-vi.gif" /> <a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/brief-history-sustainable-fashion/">Discuss This &raquo;</a></p></div></div><div
