class="post-210441 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-climate-environment category-clean-tech tag-agriculture tag-colorado tag-sustainable-agriculture" id="post-210441"><h2><a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/agriculture-drones-help-farmers-reduce-resource-use/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Agriculture Drones Help Farmers Reduce Resource Use"><span
itemprop="name">Agriculture Drones Help Farmers Reduce Resource Use</span></a></h2><div
class="meta"><div
class="authorImg"> <img
alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/014a9f0b5c2ab1ed3402e3b71878a415?s=18&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D18&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-18 photo' height='18' width='18' /></div><div
class="authorInfo"><h5><a
href="http://www.hannahmiller.net" title="Visit Hannah Miller&#8217;s website" rel="author external">Hannah Miller</a> |  Thursday February 19th, 2015 | <a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/agriculture-drones-help-farmers-reduce-resource-use/#comments" title="Comments on Agriculture Drones Help Farmers Reduce Resource Use"><span
class="dsq-postid" data-dsqidentifier="210441 http://www.triplepundit.com/?p=210441">0 Comments</span></a></h5></div></div><div
class="entry"><div
class="bottomcontainerBox" style="border:1px solid #808080;background-color:#F0F4F9;"><div
style="float:left; width:85px;padding-right:10px; margin:4px 4px 4px 4px;height:30px;"> <iframe
src="http://www.facebook.com/plugins/like.php?href=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.triplepundit.com%2F2015%2F02%2Fagriculture-drones-help-farmers-reduce-resource-use%2F&amp;layout=button_count&amp;show_faces=false&amp;width=85&amp;action=like&amp;font=verdana&amp;colorscheme=light&amp;height=21" scrolling="no" frameborder="0" style="border:none; overflow:hidden; width=85px; height:21px;" allowTransparency="true"></iframe></div><div
style="float:left; width:80px;padding-right:10px; margin:4px 4px 4px 4px;height:30px;"> <g:plusone size="medium" href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/agriculture-drones-help-farmers-reduce-resource-use/"></g:plusone></div><div
style="float:left; width:95px;padding-right:10px; margin:4px 4px 4px 4px;height:30px;"> <a
href="http://twitter.com/share" class="twitter-share-button" data-url="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/agriculture-drones-help-farmers-reduce-resource-use/"  data-text="Agriculture Drones Help Farmers Reduce Resource Use" data-count="horizontal" data-via="triplepundit">Tweet</a></div><div
style="float:left; width:105px;padding-right:10px; margin:4px 4px 4px 4px;height:30px;"><script type="in/share" data-url="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/agriculture-drones-help-farmers-reduce-resource-use/" data-counter="right"></script></div></div><div
style="clear:both"></div><div
style="padding-bottom:4px;"></div><div
id="attachment_210447" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignright"><img
class="wp-image-210447 size-medium" src="http://cdn8.triplepundit.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/Agribotix-drone-created-fertilizer-prescription-map-300x172.png" alt="Map created by drone using near infrared" width="300" height="172" /><p
class="wp-caption-text">Drone-created map used to measure fertilizer needs.</p></div><p>Boulder, Colorado-based <a
href="http://agribotix.com/">Agribotix</a> is helping farmers save money and conserve water and resources in a new way: by flying drones over their fields to measure crop density, growth and many other factors. Why does this work? Because drones are able to see things that are not as obvious from the traditional line-of-sight on the ground.</p><p>Agribotix, founded last year, works with farmers in Colorado like this: They send up drones over a field, fly over and capture photo, infrared and other data, and then land after about 20 minutes. The data is then transformed into maps showing where the crops are thriving and where they aren’t.</p> <a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/agriculture-drones-help-farmers-reduce-resource-use/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Agriculture Drones Help Farmers Reduce Resource Use"> Click to continue reading &raquo;</a><p
class="more"><img
src="http://www.triplepundit.com/wp-content/themes/triplepunditv2/images/page_white_text.png"  alt="Permalink" /> <a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/agriculture-drones-help-farmers-reduce-resource-use/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Agriculture Drones Help Farmers Reduce Resource Use"> CONTINUES &raquo;</a> <img
alt="discuss" src="http://www.triplepundit.com/wp-content/themes/triplepunditv2/images/usergroup2-vi.gif" /> <a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/agriculture-drones-help-farmers-reduce-resource-use/">Discuss This &raquo;</a></p></div></div><div
class="post-210579 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-climate-environment category-people-society tag-agriculture tag-fair-trade tag-flowers tag-leon-kaye" id="post-210579"><h2><a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/sustainable-flower-growers-roses-among-many-thorns/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Sustainable Flower Growers Are a Few Roses Among Many Thorns"><span
itemprop="name">Sustainable Flower Growers Are a Few Roses Among Many Thorns</span></a></h2><div
class="meta"><div
class="authorImg"> <img
alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/05013821f5f184ce6326b39bb8a42d7a?s=18&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D18&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-18 photo' height='18' width='18' /></div><div
class="authorInfo"><h5><a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/author/leon-kaye/" title="Visit Leon Kaye&#8217;s website" rel="author external">Leon Kaye</a> |  Thursday February 19th, 2015 | <a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/sustainable-flower-growers-roses-among-many-thorns/#comments" title="Comments on Sustainable Flower Growers Are a Few Roses Among Many Thorns"><span
class="dsq-postid" data-dsqidentifier="210579 http://www.triplepundit.com/?p=210579">0 Comments</span></a></h5></div></div><div
class="entry"><div
class="bottomcontainerBox" style="border:1px solid #808080;background-color:#F0F4F9;"><div
style="float:left; width:85px;padding-right:10px; margin:4px 4px 4px 4px;height:30px;"> <iframe
src="http://www.facebook.com/plugins/like.php?href=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.triplepundit.com%2F2015%2F02%2Fsustainable-flower-growers-roses-among-many-thorns%2F&amp;layout=button_count&amp;show_faces=false&amp;width=85&amp;action=like&amp;font=verdana&amp;colorscheme=light&amp;height=21" scrolling="no" frameborder="0" style="border:none; overflow:hidden; width=85px; height:21px;" allowTransparency="true"></iframe></div><div
style="float:left; width:80px;padding-right:10px; margin:4px 4px 4px 4px;height:30px;"> <g:plusone size="medium" href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/sustainable-flower-growers-roses-among-many-thorns/"></g:plusone></div><div
style="float:left; width:95px;padding-right:10px; margin:4px 4px 4px 4px;height:30px;"> <a
href="http://twitter.com/share" class="twitter-share-button" data-url="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/sustainable-flower-growers-roses-among-many-thorns/"  data-text="Sustainable Flower Growers Are a Few Roses Among Many Thorns" data-count="horizontal" data-via="triplepundit">Tweet</a></div><div
style="float:left; width:105px;padding-right:10px; margin:4px 4px 4px 4px;height:30px;"><script type="in/share" data-url="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/sustainable-flower-growers-roses-among-many-thorns/" data-counter="right"></script></div></div><div
style="clear:both"></div><div
style="padding-bottom:4px;"></div><div
id="attachment_210580" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignright"><img
class="size-medium wp-image-210580" src="http://cdn8.triplepundit.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/Billions-of-flowers-pass-through-the-Aalsmeer-Flower-Auction-in-the-Netherlands-300x225.jpg" alt="Fair trade, flowers, sustainable flowers, floriculture, Leon Kaye, Columbia, slow flowers, Certified American grown program" width="300" height="225" /><p
class="wp-caption-text">Billions of flowers pass through the Aalsmeer Flower Auction in the Netherlands</p></div><p>If you are irritated because Valentine’s Day flowers are already dying, take a step back and consider the journey they took to get from farm to vase. In the U.S., most of the flowers sold are grown in Colombia and Ecuador; regular reports estimate that 80 percent of cut flowers sold in the U.S. are imports. Across the pond in Europe, the Netherlands ranks as <a
href="http://www.worldstopexports.com/flower-bouquet-exports-country/3307">the largest exporter</a>, thanks in part to its enormous flower auction house in Aalsmeer, where flowers from elsewhere in Europe, Africa and Asia are traded and sold.</p><p>The fact you got flowers at all is the result of their journey by airplane, underlying the massive carbon footprint of the industry. But there is also a massive effect on people — and that footprint is more like a boot on the neck. As many journalists have demonstrated, most recently in the <a
href="http://www.theguardian.com/sustainable-business/2015/feb/12/the-women-suffering-for-your-valentines-day-flowers">Guardian</a>, the hours floriculture workers endure are long, the conditions often terrible and the pay low. So, if you’re considering flowers for upcoming Easter, Passover, Mother’s Day, or for that birthday or milestone, you may want to take a look at some of the more responsible flower vendors that are on the market.</p> <a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/sustainable-flower-growers-roses-among-many-thorns/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Sustainable Flower Growers Are a Few Roses Among Many Thorns"> Click to continue reading &raquo;</a><p
class="more"><img
src="http://www.triplepundit.com/wp-content/themes/triplepunditv2/images/page_white_text.png"  alt="Permalink" /> <a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/sustainable-flower-growers-roses-among-many-thorns/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Sustainable Flower Growers Are a Few Roses Among Many Thorns"> CONTINUES &raquo;</a> <img
alt="discuss" src="http://www.triplepundit.com/wp-content/themes/triplepunditv2/images/usergroup2-vi.gif" /> <a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/sustainable-flower-growers-roses-among-many-thorns/">Discuss This &raquo;</a></p></div></div><div
