class="meta"><div
class="authorImg"> <img
alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/05013821f5f184ce6326b39bb8a42d7a?s=18&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D18&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-18 photo' height='18' width='18' /></div><div
class="authorInfo"><h5><a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/author/leon-kaye/" title="Visit Leon Kaye&#8217;s website" rel="author external">Leon Kaye</a> |  Wednesday February 18th, 2015 | <a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/gm-wind-energy-mexico/#comments" title="Comments on GM Adds Wind Energy to Power Factories in Mexico"><span
class="dsq-postid" data-dsqidentifier="210461 http://www.triplepundit.com/?p=210461">1 Comment</span></a></h5></div></div><div
class="entry"><div
class="bottomcontainerBox" style="border:1px solid #808080;background-color:#F0F4F9;"><div
style="float:left; width:85px;padding-right:10px; margin:4px 4px 4px 4px;height:30px;"> <iframe
src="http://www.facebook.com/plugins/like.php?href=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.triplepundit.com%2F2015%2F02%2Fgm-wind-energy-mexico%2F&amp;layout=button_count&amp;show_faces=false&amp;width=85&amp;action=like&amp;font=verdana&amp;colorscheme=light&amp;height=21" scrolling="no" frameborder="0" style="border:none; overflow:hidden; width=85px; height:21px;" allowTransparency="true"></iframe></div><div
style="float:left; width:80px;padding-right:10px; margin:4px 4px 4px 4px;height:30px;"> <g:plusone size="medium" href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/gm-wind-energy-mexico/"></g:plusone></div><div
style="float:left; width:95px;padding-right:10px; margin:4px 4px 4px 4px;height:30px;"> <a
href="http://twitter.com/share" class="twitter-share-button" data-url="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/gm-wind-energy-mexico/"  data-text="GM Adds Wind Energy to Power Factories in Mexico" data-count="horizontal" data-via="triplepundit">Tweet</a></div><div
style="float:left; width:105px;padding-right:10px; margin:4px 4px 4px 4px;height:30px;"><script type="in/share" data-url="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/gm-wind-energy-mexico/" data-counter="right"></script></div></div><div
style="clear:both"></div><div
style="padding-bottom:4px;"></div><div
id="attachment_210462" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignright"><img
class="size-medium wp-image-210462" src="http://cdn7.triplepundit.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/GM-is-partnering-with-Enel-to-use-wind-power-to-power-its-factoris-in-Mexico-300x200.jpeg" alt="GM, General Motors, climate change, renewable energy, wind power, wind energy, Palo Alto, Mexico, clean energy, renewables, Enel Green Power, Leon Kaye" width="300" height="200" /><p
class="wp-caption-text">GM is partnering with Enel to use wind power to power its factoris in Mexico</p></div><p>Yesterday <a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/topic/general-motors/">General Motors</a> (GM) announced it will add wind power to its energy portfolio for the first time in the history of the company. The construction of the <a
href="http://media.gm.com/media/us/en/gm/news.detail.html/content/Pages/news/us/en/2015/feb/0217-windfarm.html">34 megawatt wind farm</a> in Palo Alto, 325 miles (526 km) from Mexico City, will begin during the second quarter of this year.</p><p>When complete, 75 percent of the wind farm’s energy will power GM’s 104 acre factory and plant facilities in Toluca, an hour’s drive west of Mexico City. The wind energy will also provide some electricity for other GM plants in Silao, San Luis Petosi and Ramos Arizpe. <a
href="http://www.enelgreenpower.com/en-GB/">Enel Green Power</a>, the US$2.3 billion dollar renewable energy company based in Italy, has designed and will build the plant as directed in a purchase power agreement signed with GM.</p> <a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/gm-wind-energy-mexico/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to GM Adds Wind Energy to Power Factories in Mexico"> Click to continue reading &raquo;</a><p
class="more"><img
src="http://www.triplepundit.com/wp-content/themes/triplepunditv2/images/page_white_text.png"  alt="Permalink" /> <a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/gm-wind-energy-mexico/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to GM Adds Wind Energy to Power Factories in Mexico"> CONTINUES &raquo;</a> <img
alt="discuss" src="http://www.triplepundit.com/wp-content/themes/triplepunditv2/images/usergroup2-vi.gif" /> <a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/gm-wind-energy-mexico/">Discuss This &raquo;</a></p></div></div><div
class="post-210389 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-climate-environment tag-as-you-sow tag-california tag-chocolate tag-food-and-agriculture tag-hershey tag-lead tag-mars-inc tag-toxic-chemicals" id="post-210389"><h2><a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/lead-cadmium-found-popular-chocolate-candies/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Lead and Cadmium Found in Popular Chocolate Candies"><span
itemprop="name">Lead and Cadmium Found in Popular Chocolate Candies</span></a></h2><div
class="meta"><div
class="authorImg"> <img
alt='Gina-Marie Cheeseman' src='http://www.triplepundit.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Gina-Marie-Cheeseman_avatar_1382062833-18x18.jpg' class='avatar avatar-18 photo' height='18' width='18' /></div><div
class="authorInfo"><h5><a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/author/ginamarie/"><span
itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person"> <span
itemprop="name">Gina-Marie Cheeseman</span></a> |  Wednesday February 18th, 2015 | <a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/lead-cadmium-found-popular-chocolate-candies/#comments" title="Comments on Lead and Cadmium Found in Popular Chocolate Candies"><span
class="dsq-postid" data-dsqidentifier="210389 http://www.triplepundit.com/?p=210389">1 Comment</span></a></h5></div></div><div
class="entry"><div
class="bottomcontainerBox" style="border:1px solid #808080;background-color:#F0F4F9;"><div
style="float:left; width:85px;padding-right:10px; margin:4px 4px 4px 4px;height:30px;"> <iframe
src="http://www.facebook.com/plugins/like.php?href=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.triplepundit.com%2F2015%2F02%2Flead-cadmium-found-popular-chocolate-candies%2F&amp;layout=button_count&amp;show_faces=false&amp;width=85&amp;action=like&amp;font=verdana&amp;colorscheme=light&amp;height=21" scrolling="no" frameborder="0" style="border:none; overflow:hidden; width=85px; height:21px;" allowTransparency="true"></iframe></div><div
style="float:left; width:80px;padding-right:10px; margin:4px 4px 4px 4px;height:30px;"> <g:plusone size="medium" href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/lead-cadmium-found-popular-chocolate-candies/"></g:plusone></div><div
style="float:left; width:95px;padding-right:10px; margin:4px 4px 4px 4px;height:30px;"> <a
href="http://twitter.com/share" class="twitter-share-button" data-url="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/lead-cadmium-found-popular-chocolate-candies/"  data-text="Lead and Cadmium Found in Popular Chocolate Candies" data-count="horizontal" data-via="triplepundit">Tweet</a></div><div
style="float:left; width:105px;padding-right:10px; margin:4px 4px 4px 4px;height:30px;"><script type="in/share" data-url="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/lead-cadmium-found-popular-chocolate-candies/" data-counter="right"></script></div></div><div
style="clear:both"></div><div
style="padding-bottom:4px;"></div><p><img
class="alignright size-medium wp-image-210391" src="http://cdn7.triplepundit.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/Chocolate-300x234.jpg" alt="Chocolate" width="300" height="234" />There’s just nothing like a bar of chocolate. As a consummate and passionate chocolate lover, I am dismayed to learn that I might be ingesting lead and cadmium when I eat a chocolate bar.</p><p>The nonprofit foundation As You Sow <a
href="http://www.asyousow.org/our-work/environmental-health/toxic-enforcement/lead-and-cadmium-in-food/" target="_blank">tested 42 chocolate products</a> for lead and cadmium, and found that 26 of them (62 percent) have lead and/or cadmium in levels that violate <a
href="http://oehha.ca.gov/prop65/background/p65plain.html" target="_blank">California’s Proposition 65 law</a>. Under Proposition 65, companies are required to warn consumers about significant amounts of chemicals present in the products they buy. Proposition 65 also requires the state to publish a <a
href="http://oehha.ca.gov/prop65/prop65_list/files/P65single012315.p" target="_blank">list</a> of chemicals known to cause cancer, birth defects or other reproductive harm. Both lead and cadmium are on the list.</p><p><a
href="http://www.asyousow.org/" target="_blank">As You Sow</a> filed notices of legal action with 16 manufacturers for not providing the required warnings that their chocolate products contain lead, cadmium or both. The companies include <a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/topic/hershey/" target="_blank">Hershey</a>, See’s Candies, <a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/topic/mars-inc/" target="_blank">Mars</a> and Godiva. The reason As You Sow filed the legal notices is because “consumers need to know that chocolate may contain heavy metals,” Eleanne van Vliet, As You Sow’s toxic chemical research director, said in a <a
href="http://www.asyousow.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/release-toxic-chocolate-valentine-surprise.pdf" target="_blank">statement</a>.</p> <a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/lead-cadmium-found-popular-chocolate-candies/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Lead and Cadmium Found in Popular Chocolate Candies"> Click to continue reading &raquo;</a><p
class="more"><img
src="http://www.triplepundit.com/wp-content/themes/triplepunditv2/images/page_white_text.png"  alt="Permalink" /> <a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/lead-cadmium-found-popular-chocolate-candies/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Lead and Cadmium Found in Popular Chocolate Candies"> CONTINUES &raquo;</a> <img
alt="discuss" src="http://www.triplepundit.com/wp-content/themes/triplepunditv2/images/usergroup2-vi.gif" /> <a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/lead-cadmium-found-popular-chocolate-candies/">Discuss This &raquo;</a></p></div></div><div
class="post-210278 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-people-society tag-eco-tourism-ecuador tag-ecotourism tag-ecuador tag-travel" id="post-210278"><h2><a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/visiting-indigenous-ecuadorian-highlands/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Visiting the Indigenous Ecuadorian Highlands"><span
itemprop="name">Visiting the Indigenous Ecuadorian Highlands</span></a></h2><div
class="meta"><div
class="authorImg"> <img
alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/0610cc9b07f8377afc956726e94343c9?s=18&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D18&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-18 photo' height='18' width='18' /></div><div
class="authorInfo"><h5><a
href="http://www.SarahLozanova.com" title="Visit Sarah Lozanova&#8217;s website" rel="author external">Sarah Lozanova</a> |  Wednesday February 18th, 2015 | <a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/visiting-indigenous-ecuadorian-highlands/#comments" title="Comments on Visiting the Indigenous Ecuadorian Highlands"><span
class="dsq-postid" data-dsqidentifier="210278 http://www.triplepundit.com/?p=210278">0 Comments</span></a></h5></div></div><div
class="entry"><div
class="bottomcontainerBox" style="border:1px solid #808080;background-color:#F0F4F9;"><div
style="float:left; width:85px;padding-right:10px; margin:4px 4px 4px 4px;height:30px;"> <iframe
src="http://www.facebook.com/plugins/like.php?href=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.triplepundit.com%2F2015%2F02%2Fvisiting-indigenous-ecuadorian-highlands%2F&amp;layout=button_count&amp;show_faces=false&amp;width=85&amp;action=like&amp;font=verdana&amp;colorscheme=light&amp;height=21" scrolling="no" frameborder="0" style="border:none; overflow:hidden; width=85px; height:21px;" allowTransparency="true"></iframe></div><div
style="float:left; width:80px;padding-right:10px; margin:4px 4px 4px 4px;height:30px;"> <g:plusone size="medium" href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/visiting-indigenous-ecuadorian-highlands/"></g:plusone></div><div
style="float:left; width:95px;padding-right:10px; margin:4px 4px 4px 4px;height:30px;"> <a
href="http://twitter.com/share" class="twitter-share-button" data-url="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/visiting-indigenous-ecuadorian-highlands/"  data-text="Visiting the Indigenous Ecuadorian Highlands" data-count="horizontal" data-via="triplepundit">Tweet</a></div><div
style="float:left; width:105px;padding-right:10px; margin:4px 4px 4px 4px;height:30px;"><script type="in/share" data-url="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/visiting-indigenous-ecuadorian-highlands/" data-counter="right"></script></div></div><div
style="clear:both"></div><div
style="padding-bottom:4px;"></div><div
style="text-align: right; text-size: .9em;"><a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/topic/eco-tourism-ecuador"><img
class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-202381" src="http://cdn6.triplepundit.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/eco-tourism-3p-650x75.gif" alt="eco-tourism-3p" width="650" height="75" />Read more in this series</a></div><p><img
class="alignright size-medium wp-image-210397" src="http://cdn7.triplepundit.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/potatoes-224x300.jpg" alt="Otavalo ecotourism" width="224" height="300" /></p><p>During our <a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/topic/eco-tourism-ecuador/" target="_blank">ecotourism adventure in Ecuador</a>, my family found ourselves in the highlands of the Andes, along the slopes of the now dormant Cotacachi Volcano. This area around Otavalo, Ecuador is dotted with adobe villages with large indigenous populations, where the Kichwa language and traditional dress are widespread. Oven-baked adobe bricks, elders carrying firewood through the countryside barefoot and large family gardens abound.</p><p>In recent decades, however, many people have left the area to seek educational and employment opportunities &#8212; resulting in greater wealth but also a loss in cultural heritage. Use of the <a
href="http://www.uni-koeln.de/gbs/Berichte/VanderMolenSkarbo_Kichwa.pdf" target="_blank">Kichwa language is in decline</a>, as many young people do not learn the language.</p><p><a
href="http://www.runatupari.com/" target="_blank">Runa Tupari</a> is a community-based tourism agency with a vision for creating economic opportunities in these rural indigenous communities, while celebrating the local indigenous cultures in a respectful cultural exchange. The organization is creating economic opportunities in the community that help affirm this sustainable way of life, where homegrown native foods, community bonds that span generations and a vibrant culture can thrive.</p> <a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/visiting-indigenous-ecuadorian-highlands/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Visiting the Indigenous Ecuadorian Highlands"> Click to continue reading &raquo;</a><p
class="more"><img
src="http://www.triplepundit.com/wp-content/themes/triplepunditv2/images/page_white_text.png"  alt="Permalink" /> <a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/visiting-indigenous-ecuadorian-highlands/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Visiting the Indigenous Ecuadorian Highlands"> CONTINUES &raquo;</a> <img
alt="discuss" src="http://www.triplepundit.com/wp-content/themes/triplepunditv2/images/usergroup2-vi.gif" /> <a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/visiting-indigenous-ecuadorian-highlands/">Discuss This &raquo;</a></p></div></div><div
class="post-210418 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-investment-markets category-economics tag-capital-markets tag-investment tag-social-enterprise tag-social-entrepreneurs tag-venture-capital" id="post-210418"><h2><a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/growth-financing-social-enterprises-5-options-make-work/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Growth Financing for Social Enterprises: 5 Options and How to Make Them Work for You"><span
itemprop="name">Growth Financing for Social Enterprises: 5 Options and How to Make Them Work for You</span></a></h2><div
class="meta"><div
class="authorImg"> <img
alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/247c685dfad19a8d0af7a29cb9eac9dc?s=18&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D18&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-18 photo' height='18' width='18' /></div><div
class="authorInfo"><h5><a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/writers/" title="Visit 3p Contributor&#8217;s website" rel="author external">3p Contributor</a> |  Wednesday February 18th, 2015 | <a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/growth-financing-social-enterprises-5-options-make-work/#comments" title="Comments on Growth Financing for Social Enterprises: 5 Options and How to Make Them Work for You"><span
class="dsq-postid" data-dsqidentifier="210418 http://www.triplepundit.com/?p=210418">1 Comment</span></a></h5></div></div><div
class="entry"><div
class="bottomcontainerBox" style="border:1px solid #808080;background-color:#F0F4F9;"><div
style="float:left; width:85px;padding-right:10px; margin:4px 4px 4px 4px;height:30px;"> <iframe
src="http://www.facebook.com/plugins/like.php?href=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.triplepundit.com%2F2015%2F02%2Fgrowth-financing-social-enterprises-5-options-make-work%2F&amp;layout=button_count&amp;show_faces=false&amp;width=85&amp;action=like&amp;font=verdana&amp;colorscheme=light&amp;height=21" scrolling="no" frameborder="0" style="border:none; overflow:hidden; width=85px; height:21px;" allowTransparency="true"></iframe></div><div
style="float:left; width:80px;padding-right:10px; margin:4px 4px 4px 4px;height:30px;"> <g:plusone size="medium" href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/growth-financing-social-enterprises-5-options-make-work/"></g:plusone></div><div
style="float:left; width:95px;padding-right:10px; margin:4px 4px 4px 4px;height:30px;"> <a
href="http://twitter.com/share" class="twitter-share-button" data-url="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/growth-financing-social-enterprises-5-options-make-work/"  data-text="Growth Financing for Social Enterprises: 5 Options and How to Make Them Work for You" data-count="horizontal" data-via="triplepundit">Tweet</a></div><div
style="float:left; width:105px;padding-right:10px; margin:4px 4px 4px 4px;height:30px;"><script type="in/share" data-url="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/growth-financing-social-enterprises-5-options-make-work/" data-counter="right"></script></div></div><div
style="clear:both"></div><div
style="padding-bottom:4px;"></div><div
id="attachment_210423" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignright"><img
class="size-medium wp-image-210423" src="http://cdn8.triplepundit.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/Common-Market_sm-300x200.jpg" alt="A regional food hub funded by RSF Social Finance, Common Market in Philadelphia has grown rapidly through a series of integrated capital financings. " width="300" height="200" /><p
class="wp-caption-text">A regional food hub funded by RSF Social Finance, Common Market in Philadelphia has grown rapidly through a series of integrated capital financings.</p></div><p><strong>By Don Shaffer</strong></p><p>Social entrepreneurs seeking growth funding often get caught up in the culture of venture capital: They position their enterprise as a rocket business, look for a miracle angel investor and start giving away equity. They’re not thinking about how the investors will get their money back, or whether other options might better support their goals.</p><p>At the same time, conventional funders often see <a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/topic/social-enterprise/" target="_blank">social enterprises</a> as too risky or too hard to understand, especially if they’re building a new supply chain, sacrificing some profit to maximize social value or using a hybrid business model.</p><p>Fortunately, there are ways around traps and barriers like these for social enterprises that are past the bootstrapping stage. First, here are a few general guidelines:</p><ul><li>Before you seek financing, <strong>define what you ultimately want to do</strong>. Are you planning to sell this business? Do you see it as a legacy business that you’re building to last? A long-term, slow-growth plan won’t nix your chances for funding; you’ll just need to look at different kinds of funding.</li><li><strong>Seek out funders that focus on social enterprises</strong> and that have expertise in your field. They’ll have a better understanding of the market opportunity, and they won’t expect your business to compromise its mission in order to grow.</li><li><strong>Expect a funder to add value beyond financing</strong>, such as connections to a network of advisors or technical assistance.</li></ul><p>Below are the ins and outs of five funding options — some top of mind, and some you may not have considered.</p> <a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/growth-financing-social-enterprises-5-options-make-work/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Growth Financing for Social Enterprises: 5 Options and How to Make Them Work for You"> Click to continue reading &raquo;</a><p
class="more"><img
src="http://www.triplepundit.com/wp-content/themes/triplepunditv2/images/page_white_text.png"  alt="Permalink" /> <a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/growth-financing-social-enterprises-5-options-make-work/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Growth Financing for Social Enterprises: 5 Options and How to Make Them Work for You"> CONTINUES &raquo;</a> <img
alt="discuss" src="http://www.triplepundit.com/wp-content/themes/triplepunditv2/images/usergroup2-vi.gif" /> <a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/growth-financing-social-enterprises-5-options-make-work/">Discuss This &raquo;</a></p></div></div><div
class="post-210405 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-climate-environment category-investment-markets tag-carbon-emissions tag-climate-change tag-drugs tag-greenhouse-gas-emissions tag-keystone-xl-pipeline" id="post-210405"><h2><a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/scheme-things-war-drugs-can-teach-us-keystone-xl/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to In the Scheme of Things: What the &#8216;War on Drugs&#8217; Can Teach Us About Keystone XL"><span
itemprop="name">In the Scheme of Things: What the &#8216;War on Drugs&#8217; Can Teach Us About Keystone XL</span></a></h2><div
class="meta"><div
class="authorImg"> <img
alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/247c685dfad19a8d0af7a29cb9eac9dc?s=18&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D18&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-18 photo' height='18' width='18' /></div><div
class="authorInfo"><h5><a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/writers/" title="Visit 3p Contributor&#8217;s website" rel="author external">3p Contributor</a> |  Wednesday February 18th, 2015 | <a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/scheme-things-war-drugs-can-teach-us-keystone-xl/#comments" title="Comments on In the Scheme of Things: What the &#8216;War on Drugs&#8217; Can Teach Us About Keystone XL"><span
class="dsq-postid" data-dsqidentifier="210405 http://www.triplepundit.com/?p=210405">1 Comment</span></a></h5></div></div><div
class="entry"><div
class="bottomcontainerBox" style="border:1px solid #808080;background-color:#F0F4F9;"><div
style="float:left; width:85px;padding-right:10px; margin:4px 4px 4px 4px;height:30px;"> <iframe
