style="clear:both"></div><div
style="padding-bottom:4px;"></div><p><img
class="alignright size-medium wp-image-210407" src="http://cdn7.triplepundit.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/6320927574_8f7143ab21_b-e1424212349221-300x159.jpg" alt="Keystone XL Debate Rages 6 years and counting" width="300" height="159" /> <strong>By Joe Madden</strong></p><p>Like every other American with media access, I have no choice but to acknowledge the <a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/topic/keystone-xl-pipeline/" target="_blank">Keystone XL</a> “debate.&#8221; It is everywhere … and it has spurred impassioned pleas from environmentalists, patriotic calls to duty from conservatives and even one of <a
href="http://thedailyshow.cc.com/videos/z14ywk/keystone-fight">Jon Stewart’s more exhaustive rants</a>.</p><p>Now a bill authorizing the completion of the pipeline is poised to pass both houses and is awaiting a likely veto from President Barack Obama. <a
href="http://www.nrdc.org/energy/keystone-pipeline/">Opponents</a> argue that the pipeline will not add to U.S. energy independence and that it will contribute to climate change and a multitude of other negative environmental and social outcomes. <a
href="http://keystone-xl.com/home/transcanada-keystone-xl-pipeline-facts-kxl/">Transcanada</a>, the company seeking rights to build the pipeline, says: <em>“</em>Keystone XL Pipeline will be the safest and most advanced oil pipeline operation in North America. It will not only bring essential infrastructure to North American oil producers, but it will also provide jobs, long-term energy independence and an economic boost to Americans.”</p><p>Regardless of where one stands on the issue, the focus of the current debate is misplaced.</p> <a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/scheme-things-war-drugs-can-teach-us-keystone-xl/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to In the Scheme of Things: What the &#8216;War on Drugs&#8217; Can Teach Us About Keystone XL"> Click to continue reading &raquo;</a><p
class="more"><img
src="http://www.triplepundit.com/wp-content/themes/triplepunditv2/images/page_white_text.png"  alt="Permalink" /> <a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/scheme-things-war-drugs-can-teach-us-keystone-xl/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to In the Scheme of Things: What the &#8216;War on Drugs&#8217; Can Teach Us About Keystone XL"> CONTINUES &raquo;</a> <img
alt="discuss" src="http://www.triplepundit.com/wp-content/themes/triplepunditv2/images/usergroup2-vi.gif" /> <a
href="http://www.triplepundit.com/2015/02/scheme-things-war-drugs-can-teach-us-keystone-xl/">Discuss This &raquo;</a></p></div></div><div
